# Stella AI Extension - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API keys
# NEVER commit the .env file to version control!

# Google Gemini API Key
# Get your key at: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# YouTube Data API v3 Key
# Get your key at: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
VITE_YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_youtube_api_key_here

# Google Custom Search API Key (same as YouTube key)
VITE_CUSTOM_SEARCH_KEY=your_custom_search_api_key_here

# Custom Search Engine ID
# Create at: https://programmablesearchengine.google.com/
VITE_SEARCH_ENGINE_ID=your_search_engine_id_here

# ========================================
# Setup Instructions:
# ========================================
#
# 1. GEMINI API:
#    - Visit https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#    - Create a new API key
#    - Copy and paste it above
#
# 2. YOUTUBE DATA API:
#    - Visit https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library
#    - Search for "YouTube Data API v3"
#    - Enable the API
#    - Go to Credentials and create an API key
#    - Copy and paste it above
#
# 3. CUSTOM SEARCH API:
#    - Use the same key as YouTube API
#    - Visit https://programmablesearchengine.google.com/
#    - Click "Add" to create a new search engine
#    - Add "www.google.com" as a site to search (for general web search)
#    - Enable "Search the entire web"
#    - Copy the Search Engine ID and paste it above
#
# 4. ENABLE APIS IN GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE:
#    - Visit https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library
#    - Enable "Custom Search API"
#    - Ensure billing is enabled (free tier is generous)
#
# ========================================
# Free Tier Limits:
# ========================================
# - Gemini API: 60 requests per minute (free)
# - YouTube API: 10,000 units per day (free)
# - Custom Search: 100 queries per day (free)
#
# ========================================
# Security Notes:
# ========================================
# - NEVER commit .env file to Git
# - Add .env to .gitignore
# - Use different keys for development and production
# - Set up API key restrictions in Google Cloud Console
